-foreign city and unit labels when selected
-auto selections (for city work, science, civics, etc) [PARTIAL — per-city "Automate citizens" toggle done (SET_CITIZEN_AUTOMATION; manual mode works only locked tiles). Auto-research / auto-civics deliberately deferred.]
-auto unit selections [DONE — input router auto-advances to the next idle unit once the active unit is done (moved/rest stance); auto_advance flag, on by default.]
-unit stack selections [DONE — see "unit stacks" above; select-all builds a multi-unit selection that orders apply across.]
-technology tree selector [DONE — tech chooser rebuilt as a tree: columns by era, rows by prereq tier, nodes show status/cost/prereqs/unlocks; researchable nodes clickable.]
-Revealed map should keep previous state until city or unit vision updates it [DONE — fog layer tracks per-player explored memory: seen tiles stay revealed under a light veil; live units shown only in current sight; memory resets on hotseat handoff.]
- add about menu (to start and pause) [DONE — About screen (title/version/license) reachable from the start menu and the pause menu.]
- advisor/info screens + UI command vocabulary [DONE — gift-unit command; sentry/heal/move-to-unit/scout-recon/air&sea-patrol unit missions; religion/corporation/turn-log/domestic-advisor/victory-progress/options/finance/military/espionage/encyclopedia screens. Deferred: camera modes, hall-of-fame/admin/world-builder, retire/chat/free-colony, unit-mission espionage, draft/trade-route. See docs/planning/designgaps.md §3.]
- starting units are wrong. check design docs, but all societies should
start with one settler, and another unit determined by starting techs
(warrior default, scout of hunting is starting tech. if this isn't in
game-data.md, add it. If starting technologies are unclear from docs,
ask user for info, then update game-data.md with this info, then continue
fixing this issue [DONE — every faction now opens with exactly a settler +
one escort: a scout if Hunting is a starting tech, else a warrior. Rule is
data-driven (constants.json starting_units_base/starting_unit_by_tech/
starting_unit_default) and applied via DataDB.starting_units_for_techs,
evaluated against each society's own starting_techs (now also seeded into
the player's known techs). Documented in game-data.md §3; the old uniform
5-unit default_starting_units list is gone.]
- all tiles should be clickable (unoccupied tiles show terrain info
on side and deselect current unit if space is invalid move for unit).
[DONE — left-click an empty/foreign tile deselects the current unit and
shows a terrain readout (SimFacade.inspect_tile / tile_info_text;
SelectionState.inspected_tile; selection panel renders it). Movement is
now right-click (see below), so left-click is purely select/inspect.]
- city should be selectable the turn it is founded (it appears to not
be selectable)
[DONE — left-click cycles a tile's own subjects (units in spawn order,
then the city), so a city sharing its tile with the founding escort is
reachable by clicking the tile again. InputRouter._subjects_at/_next_subject.]
- once a unit stack is selected, it doesn't seem possible to select
another unit or city and stack members appear inaccurate when a unit
is moved out of the stack
[DONE — left-click ALWAYS selects (never moves), so you can switch to any
other unit or city while a unit is active; movement moved to right-click.
The selection panel recomputes the on-tile stack from live state each
rebuild, so it never shows stale members.]
- after selecting first unit to leave the stack, it doesn't appear
possible to move other units out of stack
[DONE — MOVE_STACK takes an optional unit_ids subset and moves only those
(Commands.move_stack / SimFacade._stack_movers); the per-unit MISSION_MOVE_TO
command moves a single unit. Right-click passes the current selection, so
each member peels off one at a time. Empty unit_ids moves the whole stack (AI).]

Follow-up fixes (right-click movement + rendering artifact):
- Movement is now RIGHT-click only; LEFT-click is select/inspect only, so a
city or unit can again be a move *target* (right-click it) without left-click
ambiguity. Movement is also a proper per-unit command (MISSION_MOVE_TO moves
just its unit). InputRouter._handle_select_click / _handle_move_click.
- "Unknown grey squares" were mountain tiles rendering as a flat grey almost
identical to the missing-terrain placeholder. Fixed in scenes/world/world_view.gd:
mountains/hills now draw a peak glyph (_draw_peak) and mountains use a rockier
slate tone; DEFAULT_TERRAIN_COLOR is now glaring magenta so a genuinely unknown
terrain id is unmistakably a bug rather than looking like a mountain.


